<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id56be319d-2930-11f1-a4c1-c531e6569a02" identifier="/us/usc/t14/s2157"><num value="2157">§ 2157.</num><heading> Flag officers</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">During any period in which the Coast Guard is not operating as a service in the Navy, <ref href="/us/usc/t10/s1216/d">section 1216(d) of title 10</ref> does not apply with respect to flag officers of the Coast Guard.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id56be319e-2930-11f1-a4c1-c531e6569a02">(Added <ref href="/us/pl/113/281/tII/s212/a">Pub. L. 113–281, title II, § 212(a)</ref>, <date date="2014-12-18">Dec. 18, 2014</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/128/3029">128 Stat. 3029</ref>, § 296; renumbered § 2157, <ref href="/us/pl/115/282/tI/s112/b">Pub. L. 115–282, title I, § 112(b)</ref>, <date date="2018-12-04">Dec. 4, 2018</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/132/4216">132 Stat. 4216</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
